{"id":20046, "kind":"Bug", "createdAt":"2012-10-31T03:42:59.838119-07:00", "status":"Closed", "title":"XDMP-FRAGMENT on document insertion for certain path expressions when a fragment root is set", "category":"search", "severity":"Minor", "priority":{"level":"5", "title":""}, "submittedBy":{"username":"gchinchwadkar", "name":"Gajanan Chinchwadkar", "email":"Gajanan.Chinchwadkar@marklogic.com"}, "assignTo":{"username":"nobody", "name":"nobody nobody", "email":"nobody@marklogic.com"}, "description":"Steps:\r\n\r\n1. Define a string path range index on path 'a'.\r\n2. Define a fragment root on the database on 'b'.\r\n3. Insert document:\r\n     xdmp:document-insert(\"/abc.xml\",<a><b><c d='k'>C</c></b></a>)\r\n\r\nThe document cannot be inserted, we get an error XDMP-FRAGMENT. Strictly speaking, this error should not be handled by invalid-values option on the range index. The reason we get this error is that when we determine value of element 'a', we hit LinkNode. In other words, we cross fragment boundary.\r\n\r\nWe should have a different solution, for example, an option: \"ignore-fragment\"  applicable only to path indexes.", "samplequery":"", "sampledata":"", "version":"6.0-1", "tofixin":"6.0-3", "fixedin":"6.0-3", "platform":"all", "memory":"", "processors":"", "note":"", "subscribers":[{"username":"gchinchwadkar", "name":"Gajanan Chinchwadkar", "email":"Gajanan.Chinchwadkar@marklogic.com"}, {"username":"msrinivasan", "name":"Mahalakshmi Srinivasan", "email":"mahalakshmi.srinivasan@marklogic.com"}], "attachments":[], "relationships":[{"type":"", "to":""}], "clones":[20209], "cloneOf":19962, "support":{"headline":"", "supportDescription":"", "publishStatus":"Never Publish", "tickets":[], "customerImpact":{"level":"N/A", "title":""}, "workaround":""}, "tags":["search", "gchinchwadkar"], "changeHistory":[{"time":"2012-10-31T03:42:59.838119-07:00", "updatedBy":{"username":"gchinchwadkar", "name":"Gajanan Chinchwadkar", "email":"Gajanan.Chinchwadkar@marklogic.com"}, "c